HEADWORD: Duralumin
<hw>Duralumin</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[a trademark.]</ety> <def>an
aluminum-based alloy which is both light and strong, containing 4 per
cent of copper and 0.5 per cent of magnesium and smaller amounts of
iron, manganese, and silicon. It hardens with aging at room
temperature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

